gomodel:SYNGO_2029  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Synaptic clustering of the GlyR α4 subunit. \"\nGlyR α4 colocalizes with gephyrin (postsynaptic specialization marker) and bassoon (active zone marker) in the IPL.\n(Fig.7: Presynaptic small-field amacrine cells do not express GlyR α4.\nFig.8: \"Postsynaptic cells expressing the GlyR α4 subunit\"\nPostsynaptic amacrine cells express GlyR α4.\n\nThe justification of the localization of GlyR α4 comes from a combination of confocal IF and gene expression analysis.\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Diversity of glycine receptors in the mouse retina: localization of the alpha4 subunit.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2029" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

